# Package Management Guidelines

## Yarn Usage

- Only use Yarn for package management
- Do not use npm or other package managers
- Use `yarn add` for adding dependencies
- Use `yarn add -D` for development dependencies
- Maintain [yarn.lock](mdc:yarn.lock) file integrity

## Dependency Management

- Follow SOLID principles in dependency selection
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies
- Keep dependencies up to date
- Use TypeScript-compatible packages when available
- Verify package compatibility with Next.js and React versions

## Project Configuration

- Configuration files:
  - [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts
  - [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
  - [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
  - [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs) - PostCSS configuration
  - [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs) - ESLint configuration

## Script Management

- Use Yarn scripts defined in package.json
- Do not generate or use external scripts for build processes
- Keep build processes simple and maintainable